                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>St Louis</placeName>\n                                        <date>Jan 26<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 5604</date>.</p>\n                              <p>Dear Sir!</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The Directors of our Bnai-El Congregation,\n                                        elected<lb/> at our last annual meeting, whose names you\n                                        will see by the<lb/> enclosed list, have directed me to send\n                                        you our subscriptions<lb/> List and to express to you their\n                                        hope, that you will exert<lb/> yourself in behalf of our\n                                        purpose; thus far we have succeeded<lb/> in getting a pretty\n                                        good subscription here and if a little more<lb/> can be\n                                        collected we will soon be able to go to building</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Though there is frequently but little gained if\n                                        there stands<lb/> a <sic>beautifull</sic> house dedicated to\n                                        the service of God it is of<lb/> great moment for our people\n                                        here.</p>\n                              <p>As you will have perceived during your last visit to this city\n                                        and<lb/> by your editorial experience, the interest which is\n                                        felt or<lb/> manifested here for our religion, our\n                                        literature c is far below<lb/> that of any other place in\n                                        proportion to its great <sic>jewish</sic><lb/> population,\n                                        but it is no utopian hope, that if a respectable<lb/>\n                                        Synagogue is soon built, many who do not belong now to<lb/>\n                                        any <sic>israel</sic>. Congregation will join us, and so\n                                        will probably the<lb/> others, now inactive congregation,\n                                        either as a whole or as indivi<lb/>duals; more interest will\n                                        then be felt in our affairs and from<lb/> this a better\n                                        future may be anticipated.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bn9xv3w/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
